text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia ephedroides is a tree belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Juliflorae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia.The weeping tree typically grows to a height of 1 to 4 metres (3 to 13 ft) with minni ritchi peeling bark. It blooms from August to October producing yellow flowers.
